GIT NOTES – FULL WORKFLOW (INITIAL PUSH, LOCAL BRANCHES, REMOTE BRANCHES, PULL REQUESTS)

------------------------------------------------------------
1. HOW TO PUSH INITIAL PROJECT TO GITHUB
------------------------------------------------------------

Step 1: Open CMD in your project folder (must contain pom.xml)
    cd "C:\path\to\your\project"

Step 2: Initialize Git
    git init

Step 3: Add remote GitHub repo
    git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/<repo>.git

Step 4: Add all project files
    git add .

Step 5: Commit files
    git commit -m "Initial commit"

Step 6: Push to GitHub (main branch)
    git push -u origin main
If your branch is master:
    git push -u origin master

------------------------------------------------------------
2. HOW TO FETCH REMOTE BRANCHES
------------------------------------------------------------

Fetch all branches from GitHub:
    git fetch --all

List remote branches:
    git branch -r

List both local + remote branches:
    git branch -a

------------------------------------------------------------
3. HOW TO CREATE A LOCAL BRANCH FROM REMOTE BRANCH
------------------------------------------------------------

Create local branch tracking remote:
    git checkout -b MyLocalBranch origin/RemoteBranchName

Example:
    git checkout -b RB_One_local origin/RB_One

Check current branch:
    git branch

------------------------------------------------------------
4. HOW TO CREATE A LOCAL FEATURE BRANCH (RECOMMENDED)
------------------------------------------------------------

Start from your latest main branch:
    git checkout main
    git pull origin main

Create a new feature branch:
    git checkout -b feature_mywork

Make code changes…

Stage and commit:
    git add .
    git commit -m "My work added"

Push feature branch to GitHub:
    git push -u origin feature_mywork

------------------------------------------------------------
5. HOW TO CREATE PULL REQUEST (PR)
------------------------------------------------------------

Once feature branch is pushed:
Go to GitHub → Your Repository
Click “Compare & Pull Request”

Set PR details:
    Base branch: main (or RB_One)
    Compare branch: feature_mywork

Submit PR.
After review → Merge PR.

------------------------------------------------------------
6. HOW TO SYNC AFTER MERGE
------------------------------------------------------------

Switch to main:
    git checkout main

Pull latest changes:
    git pull origin main

------------------------------------------------------------
7. COMMON GIT COMMANDS
------------------------------------------------------------

Check current branch:
    git branch

Switch branches:
    git checkout branchName

Delete local branch:
    git branch -d branchName

Delete remote branch:
    git push origin --delete branchName

Check remotes:
    git remote -v

Remove existing remote:
    git remote remove origin

Re-add remote:
    git remote add origin <repo-url>

------------------------------------------------------------
8. COMPLETE PULL REQUEST WORKFLOW SUMMARY
------------------------------------------------------------

1. git checkout main
2. git pull origin main
3. git checkout -b feature_newTask
4. (make changes)
5. git add .
6. git commit -m "Completed new task"
7. git push -u origin feature_newTask
8. Create PR → merge into main
9. git checkout main
10. git pull origin main

------------------------------------------------------------
END OF NOTES
------------------------------------------------------------
